What model are you using? Please attach the model and test data so that we can debug.

@pranavsharma  Here is a link to onnx model and a few image examples. Onnx model was exported from customvision.ai
https://videoindex.blob.core.windows.net/html/model-data.zip 

Code example of invocation:
```
import glob
import os
import numpy as np
import onnxruntime as rt
import cv2
from datetime import datetime
import ntpath
import time


def main(arg):
	sess = rt.InferenceSession('apex11.onnx')   
	img1 = "out-up11736592.jpg"
	

	img = cv2.imread(img1)	

	ximg224 = cv2.resize(img, (224, 224))

	ximg = ximg224[None, :, :, :] #numpy.expand_dims(ximg224, axis=0)
	ximg = (ximg).astype(np.float32)

	ximg =np.rollaxis(ximg, 3, 1) 
	
	start = time.time()
	
	input_name = sess.get_inputs()[0].name
	res = sess.run(None, {input_name: ximg})
	prob = res[0]
	
	end = time.time()
	
	print(prob)
	print(end - start)

if __name__ == "__main__":
	import sys
	main(sys.argv[1])

```
